search_results.title: Tychicus
search_results.snippet: Tychicus was an Asiatic Christian who, with Trophimus, accompanied the Apostle Paul on a part of his journey from Macedonia to Jerusalem.

search_results.title: Who was the New Testament's Tychicus?
search_results.snippet: Tychicus may have been one of Paul's students during the more than two years the apostle spent preaching and teaching in Ephesus.

search_results.title: Hello My Name Is Tychicus - Paula Wiseman
search_results.snippet: Tychicus stands as an example of a beloved, faithful servant who served not only his Lord but devoted his life to serving the body of Christ.
